Package net.jandie1505.playerlevels.core.rewards.types

Klasse CommandReward

java.lang.Object
net.jandie1505.playerlevels.core.rewards.types.CommandReward
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
RewardDescriptionProvider, RewardExecutor
public class CommandReward extends Object implements RewardExecutor, RewardDescriptionProvider
This is a reward that executes a command when it is applied.
You can get the data using createMilestone(String, boolean, SenderType, Component, int) or createMilestone(String, boolean, SenderType, Component, int).

    • onApply

      public boolean onApply(@NotNull @NotNull Reward reward, @NotNull @NotNull Leveler player, int level)
      Beschreibung aus Schnittstelle kopiert: RewardExecutor
      This method is called when the reward is applied to the player.
      This method should do the things the reward does when it gets applied.
      If the upgrade has successfully been applied, this method has to return true. If it failed, it has to return false. This is important!
      Angegeben von:

      Parameter:

      player - player
      level - the level the reward is applied for

      Creates an interval reward data for this command reward.
      The reward data can be registered at RewardsManager.addIntervalReward(RewardConfig, IntervalRewardData).
      Parameter:
      command - the command that should be executed
      requiresOnlinePlayer - if the command requires the player to be online
      senderType - CommandReward.SenderType
      description - reward description
      start - interval start
      interval - interval in levels the player should get the reward applied
      limit - the reward will not be applied for levels higher/equal than this
